"title": "7963: song",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7963: song",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In Scripture, songs express praise, thanksgiving, joy, victory and love. They also express sadness and derision and can be used to teach and warn. In heaven believers will sing a new song to God.</p>\n<h2>Different kinds of song</h2>\n<h3>Songs of praise and thanksgiving</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr5:13\">2CH 5:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:30\">PSA 69:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:8\">NEH 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh12:46\">NEH 12:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps28:7\">PSA 28:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:2\">PSA 95:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer30:18-Jer30:19\">JER 30:18–30:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah2:9\">JON 2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas5:13\">JAS 5:13</a></p>\n<h3>Songs of joy and celebration</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:4\">PSA 98:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:5\">2SA 6:5</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr13:8\">1CH 13:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr15:16\">1CH 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps100:2\">PSA 100:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:22\">PSA 107:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps126:2\">PSA 126:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps126:6\">PSA 126:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa52:9\">ISA 52:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa55:12\">ISA 55:12</a></p>\n<h3>Songs of victory and deliverance</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:1-Exod15:18\">EXO 15:1–15:18</a></strong> <em>The song celebrating God's spectacular victory over Pharaoh and his army (compare with <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3\">Rev 15:3</a>).</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:1-Judg5:3\">JDG 5:1–5:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:6-1Sam18:7\">1SA 18:6–18:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam22:1-2Sam22:4\">2SA 22:1–22:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps18:2\">PSA 18:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps32:7\">PSA 32:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps42:8\">PSA 42:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:15\">PSA 118:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa26:1\">ISA 26:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa44:23\">ISA 44:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:13\">ISA 49:13</a></p>\n<h3>Psalms and hymns</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:16\">COL 3:16</a></strong> <em>“psalms, hymns and spiritual songs” are not clearly distinguished from each other in Scripture.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:7\">1CH 16:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:3\">PSA 40:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:7\">PSA 47:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:30\">MAT 26:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:26\">MRK 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:26\">1CO 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:25\">ACT 16:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:19\">EPH 5:19</a></p>\n<h3>Songs of ascent</h3>\n<p>PSA 122:0 <em>Psalms 120–134, the so-called “Songs of Ascent”, are thought to have been sung by pilgrims on their way to Jerusalem.</em></p>\n<h3>Songs of love</h3>\n<p>PSA 45:0 <em>The title to this psalm describes it as “a wedding song”</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song1:1\">SNG 1:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa5:1\">ISA 5:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek33:32\">EZK 33:32</a></p>\n<h3>Laments</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:17-2Sam1:19\">2SA 1:17–1:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:33-2Sam3:34\">2SA 3:33–3:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr35:25\">2CH 35:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps102:1-Ps102:2\">PSA 102:1–102:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:29\">JER 7:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:10\">JER 9:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:20\">JER 9:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam2:5\">LAM 2:5</a> <em>The book of Lamentations is a series of laments after the fall of Jerusalem</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:1\">EZK 19:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek19:14\">EZK 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek26:17-Ezek26:18\">EZK 26:17–26:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:2\">EZK 27:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek27:32\">EZK 27:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek28:12\">EZK 28:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek32:16\">EZK 32:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:1\">AMO 5:1</a></p>\n<h3>Songs of derision</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:9\">JOB 30:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps69:12\">PSA 69:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:14\">LAM 3:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:63\">LAM 3:63</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic2:4\">MIC 2:4</a></p>\n<h2>God is described as the song of believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps118:14\">PSA 118:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod15:2\">EXO 15:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa12:2\">ISA 12:2</a></p>\n<h2>Songs can teach and warn</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:44-Deut32:46\">DEU 32:44–32:46</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:19\">DEU 31:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:22\">DEU 31:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:30\">DEU 31:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:54\">PSA 119:54</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:19\">EPH 5:19</a></p>\n<h2>A new song</h2>\n<h3>Singing a new song to God expresses a renewed desire to praise him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps40:1-Ps40:3\">PSA 40:1–40:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps33:3\">PSA 33:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps98:1\">PSA 98:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps144:9\">PSA 144:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps149:1\">PSA 149:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:10\">ISA 42:10</a></p>\n<h3>In heaven God's people will sing a new song</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9-Rev5:10\">REV 5:9–5:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:3\">REV 14:3</a></p>",
